set.seed(2395)
library(caret)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Loading required package: lattice
library(mlbench)
library(gbm)
## Loaded gbm 2.1.8
library(C50)

# Import data sets
complete <- read.csv("CompleteResponses.csv")
incomplete <- read.csv("SurveyIncomplete.csv")

# Check for NA values
sum(is.na(complete))
## [1] 0
sum(is.na(incomplete))
## [1] 0
# Check structure of dataset
str(complete)

str(incomplete)
## 'data.frame':    5000 obs. of  7 variables:

# Converting the dependent variable to categorical
complete$brand <- as.factor(complete$brand)
incomplete$brand <- as.factor(incomplete$brand)

# Change class names to make them valid R variables
levels(complete$brand)=c("Acer", "Sony")
levels(incomplete$brand)=c("Acer", "Sony")

# Splitting training set into two parts based on outcome: 75% and 25%
index <- createDataPartition(complete$brand, p=0.75, list=FALSE)
trainSet <- complete[index,]
testSet <- complete[-index,]

# Check feature correlation
correlationMatrix <- cor(complete[,1:6])
print(correlationMatrix)

## integer(0)
# Feature selection using rfe in caret
control <- rfeControl(functions=rfFuncs, method="repeatedcv", repeats=3, verbose=FALSE)
target <- 'brand' 
features <- names(trainSet)[!names(trainSet) %in% target]
Cust_Pref_Profile <- rfe(trainSet[,features], trainSet[,target], rfeControl=control)
Cust_Pref_Profile     # Computationally expensive. Use varImp().

# Tuning parameters
ctrl <- trainControl(method="repeatedcv", number=10, repeats=1)

                    n.minobsinnode=c(3,5,10), interaction.depth=c(1,5,10))
